<TITLE> Current century belongs to Asia: foreign adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 11 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh foreign policy should focus on improving relations with other Asian countries, foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury said Wednesday. He said Bangladesh would lag behind if it did not adapt to a changing world order. "While relations with the US and the European Union remain key, it is also time for a focus on Asia, particularly the Gulf, former Soviet republics, ASEAN, China and Japan." "Because the current century belongs to Asia," Iftekhar said while addressing mid-level officials of different ministries at a seminar at the Foreign Service Academy in the city. "The world is changing and we need to constantly adapt to these changes, or we will lag behind," the foreign adviser said. Iftekhar said Bangladesh foreign policy had two purposesthe first was protection of sovereignty and independence, the second being to ensure the flow of external resources for development. He said Bangladesh was lucky to have "sufficient intellectual resources that must be employed in the formulation and execution of our external and domestic strategies". bdn
